  "prompt": "Can anyone help me with writing the RC6 algorithm for Visual Basic 6?",
  "response": "Here's an implementation of the RC6 block cipher algorithm in Visual Basic 6:\n\n```vb\nOption Explicit\n\n' RC6 Constants\nPrivate Const ROUNDS As Long = 20\nPrivate Const W As Long = 32 ' Word size\nPrivate Const LG_W As Long = 5 ' Log2(W)\n\n' RC6 Key Expansion Routine\nPrivate Sub RC6KeySchedule(Key() As Byte, ByVal KeyLength As Long, RoundKeys() As Long)\n    Dim L() As Long\n    Dim i As Long, j As Long, k As Long\n    Dim A As Long, B As Long\n    \n    ' Convert key to long array\n    ReDim L((KeyLength + 3) \\ 4 - 1)\n    For i = 0 To UBound(L)\n        L(i) = 0\n    Next i\n    \n    For i = KeyLength - 1 To 0 Step -1\n        L(i \\ 4) = (L(i \\ 4) * 256) Or Key(i)\n    Next i\n    \n    ' Initialize round keys\n    ReDim RoundKeys(2 * ROUNDS + 3)\n    RoundKeys(0) = &HB7E15163 ' Magic constant\n    \n    For i = 1 To 2 * ROUNDS + 3\n        RoundKeys(i) = RoundKeys(i - 1) + &H9E3779B9 ' Another magic constant\n    Next i\n    \n    ' Mix in key\n    A = 0\n    B = 0\n    i = 0\n    j = 0\n    k = 0\n    \n    Dim V As Long\n    V = 3 * Max((UBound(L) + 1), (2 * ROUNDS + 4))\n    \n    For k = 1 To V\n        A = RotateLeft((RoundKeys(i) + A + B), 3)\n        RoundKeys(i) = A\n        \n        B = RotateLeft((L(j) + A + B), (A + B))\n        L(j) = B\n        \n        i = (i + 1) Mod (2 * ROUNDS + 4)\n        j = (j + 1) Mod (UBound(L) + 1)\n    Next k\nEnd Sub\n\n' RC6 Encryption\nPrivate Sub RC6Encrypt(Plaintext() As Byte, RoundKeys() As Long, Ciphertext() As Byte)\n    Dim A As Long, B As Long, C As Long, D As Long\n    Dim i As Long, t As Long, u As Long\n    \n    ' Convert 16-byte input to 4 32-bit words\n    A = BytesToLong(Plaintext, 0)\n    B = BytesToLong(Plaintext, 4)\n    C = BytesToLong(Plaintext, 8)\n    D = BytesToLong(Plaintext, 12)\n    \n    B = B + RoundKeys(0)\n    D = D + RoundKeys(1)\n    \n    For i = 1 To ROUNDS\n        t = RotateLeft(B * (2 * B + 1), LG_W)\n        u = RotateLeft(D * (2 * D + 1), LG_W)\n        A = RotateLeft(A Xor t, u) + RoundKeys(2 * i)\n        C = RotateLeft(C Xor u, t) + RoundKeys(2 * i + 1)\n        \n        ' Rotate words\n        Dim temp As Long\n        temp = A\n        A = B\n        B = C\n        C = D\n        D = temp\n    Next i\n    \n    A = A + RoundKeys(2 * ROUNDS + 2)\n    C = C + RoundKeys(2 * ROUNDS + 3)\n    \n    ' Convert back to byte array\n    LongToBytes A, Ciphertext, 0\n    LongToBytes B, Ciphertext, 4\n    LongToBytes C, Ciphertext, 8\n    LongToBytes D, Ciphertext, 12\nEnd Sub\n\n' RC6 Decryption\nPrivate Sub RC6Decrypt(Ciphertext() As Byte, RoundKeys() As Long, Plaintext() As Byte)\n    Dim A As Long, B As Long, C As Long, D As Long\n    Dim i As Long, t As Long, u As Long\n    \n    ' Convert 16-byte input to 4 32-bit words\n    A = BytesToLong(Ciphertext, 0)\n    B = BytesToLong(Ciphertext, 4)\n    C = BytesToLong(Ciphertext, 8)\n    D = BytesToLong(Ciphertext, 12)\n    \n    C = C - RoundKeys(2 * ROUNDS + 3)\n    A = A - RoundKeys(2 * ROUNDS + 2)\n    \n    For i = ROUNDS To 1 Step -1\n        ' Rotate words back\n        Dim temp As Long\n        temp = D\n        D = C\n        C = B\n        B = A\n        A = temp\n        \n        u = RotateLeft(D * (2 * D + 1), LG_W)\n        t = RotateLeft(B * (2 * B + 1), LG_W)\n        C = RotateRight(C - RoundKeys(2 * i + 1), t) Xor u\n        A = RotateRight(A - RoundKeys(2 * i), u) Xor t\n    Next i\n    \n    D = D - RoundKeys(1)\n    B = B - RoundKeys(0)\n    \n    ' Convert back to byte array\n    LongToBytes A, Plaintext, 0\n    LongToBytes B, Plaintext, 4\n    LongToBytes C, Plaintext, 8\n    LongToBytes D, Plaintext, 12\nEnd Sub\n\n' Utility Functions\nPrivate Function RotateLeft(ByVal Value As Long, ByVal Shift As Long) As Long\n    Shift = Shift And &H1F\n    RotateLeft = ((Value * (2 ^ Shift)) Or (Value \\ (2 ^ (32 - Shift)))) And &HFFFFFFFF\nEnd Function\n\nPrivate Function RotateRight(ByVal Value As Long, ByVal Shift As Long) As Long\n    Shift = Shift And &H1F\n    RotateRight = ((Value \\ (2 ^ Shift)) Or (Value * (2 ^ (32 - Shift)))) And &HFFFFFFFF\nEnd Function\n\nPrivate Function BytesToLong(Arr() As Byte, ByVal Offset As Long) As Long\n    BytesToLong = CLng(Arr(Offset)) Or _\n                  CLng(Arr(Offset + 1)) * 256& Or _\n                  CLng(Arr(Offset + 2)) * 65536 Or _\n                  CLng(Arr(Offset + 3)) * 16777216\nEnd Function\n\nPrivate Sub LongToBytes(ByVal Value As Long, Arr() As Byte, ByVal Offset As Long)\n    Arr(Offset) = Value And &HFF\n    Arr(Offset + 1) = (Value \\ 256) And &HFF\n    Arr(Offset + 2) = (Value \\ 65536) And &HFF\n    Arr(Offset + 3) = (Value \\ 16777216) And &HFF\nEnd Sub\n\nPrivate Function Max(A As Long, B As Long) As Long\n    If A > B Then Max = A Else Max = B\nEnd Function\n\n' Example Usage\nPublic Sub TestRC6()\n    Dim Key(15) As Byte\n    Dim Plaintext(15) As Byte\n    Dim Ciphertext(15) As Byte\n    Dim Decrypted(15) As Byte\n    Dim RoundKeys() As Long\n    Dim i As Long\n    \n    ' Sample key and plaintext\n    For i = 0 To 15\n        Key(i) = i\n        Plaintext(i) = i * 16\n    Next i\n    \n    ' Key Schedule\n    RC6KeySchedule Key, 16, RoundKeys\n    \n    ' Encrypt\n    RC6Encrypt Plaintext, RoundKeys, Ciphertext\n    \n    ' Decrypt\n    RC6Decrypt Ciphertext, RoundKeys, Decrypted\nEnd Sub\n```\n\nThis implementation includes:\n1. RC6 Key Scheduling\n2. RC6 Encryption\n3. RC6 Decryption\n4. Utility functions for bit rotations and byte/long conversions\n\nKey features:\n- Uses 20 rounds\n- Supports 16-byte (128-bit) keys\n- Block size is 16 bytes (128 bits)\n\nTo use:\n1. Call `RC6KeySchedule` with your key\n2. Use `RC6Encrypt` or `RC6Decrypt` with the round keys\n\nNote: This is a basic implementation and might need additional error handling and optimization for production use.",
